t 1145","Abt 1190":"about 1190","Nether Tabley, Cheshire, England":"Nether Tabley, Cheshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Tabley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Over and Nether Tabley (Cheshire)."],"variants":[{"name":"Tapley","meanings":["English (Devon, Cheshire and Kent):","habitational name from Tapeley in Devon. The placename derives from an Old English personal name <i>Tæppa</i> + Old English <i>lēah</i> ‘wood, woodland clearing’.","variant of <b>Tabley</b>, a habitational name from Over and Nether Tabley in Cheshire. The placename derives from the Old English personal name <i>Tæbba</i> + Old English <i>lēah</i> ‘wood, woodland clearing’."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":70,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":79,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":114,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William Tabley was born about 1145, in Nether Tabley, Cheshire, England. He had at least 1 son with Beatrix Bexton. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"Circa 1145–":"umbes 1145–Surnud","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1145–Male":"1145–Surnud","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1145":"1145","1240":"1240","1150":"1150","Circa 1145":"umbes 1145","Abt 1190":"umbes 1190","Nether Tabley, Cheshire, England":"Nether Tabley, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"Circa 1145–":"noin 1145–Kuollut","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1145–Male":"1145–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1145":"1145","1240":"1240","1150":"1150","Circa 1145":"noin 1145","Abt 1190":"noin 1190","Nether Tabley, Cheshire, England":"Nether Tabley, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"Circa 1145–":"environ 1145–Décédé","1150–Female":"1150–Décédée","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1145–Male":"1145–Décédé","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1145":"1145","1240":"1240","1150":"1150","Circa 1145":"environ 1145","Abt 1190":"environ 1190","Nether Tabley, Cheshire, England":"Nether Tabley, Cheshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William Tabley est né environ 1145, à Neth